#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:183
msgid ""
"The methodology to distinguish access levels is based on authorization "
"parameters such as the roles associated with a user's account and/or group "
"membership. Kolab Groupware recommends using roles, as they are far more "
"scalable than group membership, to establish authorization to services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:188
msgid ""
"An example scenario building a hosted Kolab Groupware environment could be "
"to require additional payment for the use of ActiveSync to synchronize "
"mobile devices, whereas all other services and access levels are included in "
"a base price for the account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:193
msgid ""
"The following roles would be defined, with their associated access levels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:195
msgid "``cn=activesync-user,dc=mykolab,dc=com``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:197
msgid ""
"A user of ActiveSync. This role is typically added when the user selects the "
"option, and authorizes the user to use mobile device synchronization through "
"ActiveSync."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:201
msgid "``cn=imap-user,dc=mykolab,dc=com``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:203
msgid ""
"A regular user account. This role is typically added after the user's "
"account has received initial payment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:206
msgid "``cn=suspended-user,dc=mykolab,dc=com``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:208
msgid ""
"A suspended user has overdue payments, and could therefore not be allowed to "
"send any email any longer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:211
msgid ""
"It is generally considered prohibitively punitive to not allow the user to "
"access his/her data any longer, and therefore this is considered an "
"intermediate state for the account to allow timely recovery of full "
"functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:216
msgid ""
"A deployment could opt to also suspend delivery to the account, but should "
"bear in mind that delivery failure is likely considered data loss."
msgstr ""

