#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:241
msgid "Multi-Domain Hosted Environments and SSL Certificates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:243
msgid ""
"A hosted Kolab Groupware environment with customers registering their own "
"domain name spaces instructs them to use addresses for services in the "
"primary hosted domain by default. The primary hosted domain should have a "
"valid SSL certificate signed by a publically trusted certificate authority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:248
msgid ""
"For an example customer *example.org*, therefore, the location for the web "
"client would be https://webmail.mykolab.com, and the IMAP server would be "
"imaps://imap.mykolab.com. Users in the *example.org* domain would login "
"using their full email address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:253
msgid ""
"Should a customer require a dedicated SSL certificate to their domain, so "
"that the customer's users can use https://webmail.example.org and/or imaps://"
"imap.example.org, it is important to take into account that therefore the "
"domain name space needs to be associated with a dedicated public IP address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:258
msgid ""
"While modern browsers can deal with the HTTP host header negotiation prior "
"to encrypting the connection, most mobile devices can not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:261
msgid ""
"In other words, while https://webmail.example.org (for modern browsers) does "
"not strictly require a unique service IP address to be associated with it, "
"you must consider that https://activesync.example.org/Microsoft-Server-"
"ActiveSync does."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:265
msgid ""
"Furthermore, auto-discovery protocols often mistakenly assume addresses such "
"as https://autodiscover.example.org and https://example.org contain valid "
"automatic configuration, and sometimes fall back to, and sometimes do not "
"even have implemented at all, the query for SRV records such as "
"_autodiscover._tcp.example.org, which is eligible to contain a value "
"pointing to another web server http host address (that an SSL certificate is "
"available for)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/hosted-kolab-groupware-deployment.rst:272
msgid ""
"Using a dedicated service IP address resolves an issue with desktop clients "
"as well; The use of addresses such as ``imap.example.org`` and ``smtp."
"example.org`` would trigger an alert about the validity of the SSL "
"certificate used, if the service IP address for these DNS records pointed to "
"the same service IP address as those DNS records used for the primary hosted "
"domain."
msgstr ""

